        "message": "This commit fixes two minor issues for the docker build.\n\nThe first issue is that core-site.xml can be 0 length after\nsubstituting variables, see:\nhttps://issues.apache.org/jira/projects/CRAIL/issues/CRAIL-51\n\nThe second issue is that CRAIL_HOME points to a hardcoded version, see:\nhttps://issues.apache.org/jira/projects/CRAIL/issues/CRAIL-52\n\nTo fix these issues, the commit makes the following changes:\n\n- Read Crail version from toplevel pom.xml\n- Move Crail build directory to /home/crail\n- Point CRAIL_HOME to /home/crail\n- Use template core-site.xml.env file and subsitute environment variables\n  to a new core-site.xml file\n\nThis closes #40\n\nSigned-off-by: Adrian Schuepbach <asq@apache.org>",

        "message": "[storage-rdma] Make StoragerServer ep active to prevent orphaned CQ\n\nThe passive endpoint model caused an orphaned CQ at DataNode\nafter each client disconnect. Each new client connection caused\ncreation of another CQ. Changing to an active endpoint model\nfrees the per client CQ after client disconnect. Since the CQ is\nnot actually used (the endpoint handles only RDMA Read and\nWrite from client side), the active endpoint gets created with\nminimum resources (send/receive/completion queue size == 1),\nand the CQ event dispatcher is a nop.\n\nFixes https://issues.apache.org/jira/projects/CRAIL/issues/CRAIL-103\n\nSigned-off-by: Bernard Metzler <bmt@zurich.ibm.com>",
        "parents": [
